    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Actually `posix=(os.name == 'posix')` is helping us.  You can't use backslash to escape glob patterns in windows as it is path separator.  So, only possible way to escape globs is to quoting them.  To pass the quotes to glob, we need `posix=False` as otherwise shlex strips them off (or you can doubly quote...).  I've never used it in windows so I can only imagine, but I think these difference is for good, at least until we get decent shell parser.\n\nBTW, it seems the build failure is because of timeout\nhttps://travis-ci.org/#!/ipython/ipython/jobs/2990479/L2301\n"
  },
